author: suat
msg: -It is possible to use existing sessions in CMS Adapter services i.e submitting documents to Contenthub or using bidirectional mapping feature

-Anymore, it is not necessary to specify connection parameters like repository URL, username, password, etc... for each operation. A new service has been implemented for creating and caching sessions for one time and obtaining a session key associated with the cached session.
-Update option has been added to RDF generating method. As described in STANBOL-435, this makes possible to append the new RDF into already existing one.
